:::summary
Sparta (also called Lacedaemon) was a powerful Greek city-state renowned for its extraordinary military culture, discipline, and the virtue of its citizens. Sparta's unique social system produced the finest soldiers in the ancient world and made it Athens's great rival for the leadership of Greece. Its ethos of sacrifice, discipline, and civic duty has fascinated and inspired thinkers across the centuries.
:::

